            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <head>No. 310.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Pak Chung Yang</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 10, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I had the honor to receive to-day by the hands of
                    your secretary your note of this date, whereby you are pleased to inform me that
                    you have been appointed His Corean Majesty’s envoy extraordinary and minister
                    plenipotentiary near this Government, and that you are prepared to enter upon
                    the discharge of your duties as soon as it shall please the President to grant
                    you an audience and receive your credentials, to which end you solicit an
                    interview with me.</p>
                <pb facs="0588" n="454" xml:id="pg_454"/>
                <p>I have the honor to inform you in reply that, as I have already advised your
                    secretary, I shall be happy to receive you on Friday next, the 18th instant, at
                    12 o’clock, noon, and arrange to accompany you thereafter at an early day to
                    present your credentials to the President.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
